  "doc_id": "12987",
  "text": "In addition to ERC and hippocampus findings, frPSI was strongly associated with both volume reduction and cortical thinning in the precuneus. This is important given our previous findings that amyloid load in whole brain, and particularly the precuneus was related to frPSI in neuropsychologically normal, but elderly (and therefore, at-risk) community-dwelling elders [CITATION_1] . Minors, Palmer, and Love [CITATION_2] found that decreased perfusion in the precuneus is an early finding in AD. Indeed, Lundstrom, Ingvar, and Peterson [CITATION_3] have emphasized the precuneus in source memory and its relationship and connectivity to a number of brain regions involved in efficient cognitive processing.",
